  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package supports an Accepted decision based on validation evidence generated under ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2; the released model of record is ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7. The submitting team asserts the two builds are effectively identical, differing only in a patch-level release-candidate suffix, and that re-running validation is unnecessary.",
