      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-piv-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — centrifugal pump, 5 operating points",
      "description": "Comparison of CFD-predicted velocity magnitude and shear stress distributions against FDA-supplied PIV measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Normalized root-mean-square error (NRMSE) for velocity magnitude is 4.2% across all operating points. Hemolysis index predictions fall below the absolute clinical threshold at all 5 conditions. Monte Carlo UQ (n=500 samples) yields a 95th-percentile hemolysis index of 0.0031 g/100 L, well below the 0.01 g/100 L acceptance threshold. Validation team noted that the solver executable used for all production runs was ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, the release-candidate build finalized two weeks before the official release. The team asserts that the only change between rc2 and the released build (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7) was an update to the installer manifest and license-check routine, and therefore the numerical outputs are identical. No differential regression tests between rc2 and the released build were performed or archived.",
