      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must directly map to the clinical acceptance criterion (absolute hemolysis threshold) with documented traceability.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index and volume-averaged shear stress are the primary QoIs, both directly linked to the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L. Traceability matrix documented. Platelet activation index not assessed as a secondary QoI despite its relevance to VAD thrombosis risk. Achieved level 4; level 5 would require full secondary QoI coverage."
